events.title: Sunday Sunday Featuring Sofi Tukker
events.description: Since 2015, Sunday Sunday has welcomed thousands of people to the dance floor of one of the most iconic terraces in our city every Sunday, regardless of the context or nationality of its attendees. We are an inclusive party where the only requirement is mutual respect and a love for music. Here are some recommendations for attending:  Address: Tabaqueros 16, Centro Hist√≥rico.  Tabaqueros Street is a pedestrian transit area with a variety of shops open until 6 PM. Note that due to its proximity to different public institutions, it is a high-traffic area, so circulation may vary.  If you don't have tickets on the Sunday you decide to attend, our on-site box office sells tickets as long as capacity allows. To ensure your access, we recommend purchasing your tickets online in advance. If online pre-sale tickets are sold out, the box office will be waiting for you. We also have a cashless payment system on-site, where you can load a card at the box office and use it to order drinks at the bar. We accept both cash and credit or debit cards for these top-ups.  Located on the 6th floor, the Magic Dolphin Bar opens at 3:00 PM. Here, you can enjoy a prepared Clamato, listen to vinyl music, and have a delicious Burger Gang hamburger starting at 3 PM. It‚Äôs a great plan to chat with friends before diving into a vigorous Sunday dance session.  Sunday Sunday opens its dance floor on the 7th floor at 5:00 PM. Get ready to enjoy one of the best views of Mexico City while dancing to a variety of music genres. From Italo disco to techno, dub, and of course, plenty of house music. At Sunday Sunday, we are music lovers and are always open to what our guest DJs have to offer; we hope you are too.  Here‚Äôs a list of prohibited items. Any of these items will be removed and held by our security team during your stay:  - Animals or pets - Outside food or drinks - Fireworks - Drones or aerial vehicles - Eye drops - Perfumes - Medications without prescription - Cameras - Filming equipment - Any type of weapon or sharp objects - Drugs and narcotics - Open cigarette packs  Sunday Sunday is a harassment-free space, so if you find yourself in a risky situation within our facilities, you can approach our security team or any staff member at the bar and ticket counters. They are there to help and protect you.  For your safety, we recommend using only digital transportation platforms like Uber or Didi when leaving. You can ask our staff to locate safe pickup points. Our closing time is 1:00 AM.  We are happy to welcome you every Sunday and hope it won‚Äôt be long before your next visit. Remember, we are Always on Sunday.  Sunday Sunday Team.
